From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Jan 2023 13:34:24 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] build: version the shared objects

It's really weird that meson doesn't default do doing this

Signed-off-by: Robbie Harwood <rharwood@redhat.com>
(cherry picked from commit b92cbab48a7f1f79b6095382d605692f9cee93a6)
---
 meson.build | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/meson.build b/meson.build
index bd4c72f..28918cc 100644
--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -18,6 +18,7 @@ cdson = library('cdson', 'cdson.h',
                 'src/dump.c', 'src/sniff.c', 'src/fetch.c',
                 'src/allocation.h', 'src/unicode.h', 'src/unicode.c',
                 dependencies: deps,
+                version: meson.project_version(),
                 install: true)
 pkg = import('pkgconfig')
 pkg.generate(cdson)
